of the storage schema, so it likely belongs with the GitMeta writer or shared constants.\\n\\n- Capture orchestration is living in `cli.rs`. `record_agent_log` resolves the workdir, normalizes the transcript path, records the transcript, and performs optional association in [cli.rs:117](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/cli.rs:117). The resulting shape is `cli -> cli::record_agent_log -> capture -> gitmeta`, rather than the playbook’s `cli -> capture -> transcript -> gitmeta` flow.\\n\\n**Leave-Alone Notes**\\n\\n- The tiny feature-gated `but` bridge looks fine: agent detection stays in `but` at [lib.rs:1484](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but/src/lib.rs:1484), and `but-agentlog` stays unaware of the wider agent-detection enum.\\n\\n- Repo/path normalization is not meaningfully duplicated: workdir resolution happens once in [cli.rs:123](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/cli.rs:123), while transcript canonicalization in [capture.rs:13](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/capture.rs:13) is doing source identity/readability work.\\n\\n- `sync` validating the remote before opening GitMeta is the right order: [sync.rs:13](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/sync.rs:13) runs before [sync.rs:15](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/sync.rs:15), so missing remotes avoid local metadata side effects.\"}}\n</subagent_notification>","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-11T18:19:30.823Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"message","role":"user"}}}